---
import DocsLayout from "~/layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import CopyableCommand from "~/components/CopyableCommand.astro";
import Callout from "~/components/Callout.astro";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Copilot Chat (VS Code)"
  description="How budi tracks GitHub Copilot Chat in VS Code — data sources, PAT setup, reconciliation, and how to verify."
>
  <div class="flex max-w-2xl flex-col gap-10">
    <header>
      <p class="text-fg-dim mb-2 text-xs tracking-[0.18em] uppercase">Provider</p>
      <h1 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight sm:text-3xl">Copilot Chat (VS Code)</h1>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-3 leading-relaxed">
        VS Code's Copilot Chat stores local session data that budi tails for token counts. For
        dollar-accurate reconciliation, add a GitHub PAT scoped to billing — budi matches local
        sessions against GitHub's per-(date, model) billing buckets.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-4 flex items-center gap-2">
        <span class="chip border-accent text-accent">Live</span>
        <span class="text-fg-dim text-xs">since v8.4.0</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section>
      <h2 id="data-sources" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        Data sources
      </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4">
        <div class="card p-5">
          <h3 id="local-session" class="text-fg mb-1.5 text-sm font-medium">
            Local JSON/JSONL session data (primary)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            VS Code stores Copilot Chat conversation data locally. Budi tails these files for
            output-only token counts, model names, and conversation metadata.
          </p>
          <div class="text-fg-dim mt-3 text-xs">
            <span class="font-medium">Path:</span>
            <code
              class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg ml-1 rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
              >~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/</code
            >
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card p-5">
          <h3 id="billing-api" class="text-fg mb-1.5 text-sm font-medium">
            GitHub Billing API (supplementary)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-fg-muted text-sm leading-relaxed">
            When a GitHub PAT is configured, budi reconciles local session data against GitHub's
            per-(date, model) billing buckets for exact dollar amounts.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="what-is-parsed" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        What's parsed
      </h2>
      <ul class="text-fg-muted space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Output token counts per message (input tokens not exposed by VS Code)
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Model name and version
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Dollar cost (from GitHub Billing API when PAT is configured, otherwise token-estimated)
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Session boundaries and conversation timestamps
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Workspace context for repo/branch attribution
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="pat-setup" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">
        GitHub PAT setup
      </h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        Without a PAT, you get output-only token dollars — useful as a relative trend, but typically
        a fraction of the actual bill. With a PAT scoped to billing, budi reconciles to GitHub's
        exact dollar number per (date, model) bucket.
      </p>
      <ol class="text-fg-muted space-y-4 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent-soft text-accent inline-flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full font-mono text-xs font-semibold"
            >1</span
          >
          <span>
            Go to GitHub Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens → Fine-grained
            tokens.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent-soft text-accent inline-flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full font-mono text-xs font-semibold"
            >2</span
          >
          <span>
            Create a token with the <code
              class="bg-surface-3 border-line/70 text-fg rounded border px-1.5 py-0.5 text-[0.9em]"
              >billing:read</code
            > scope. No other scopes are needed.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent-soft text-accent inline-flex h-6 w-6 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-full font-mono text-xs font-semibold"
            >3</span
          >
          <span> Pass it to budi: </span>
        </li>
      </ol>
      <div class="mt-3">
        <CopyableCommand
          command="budi config set github.pat ghp_your_token_here"
          variant="compact"
        />
      </div>
      <Callout kind="warn" title="Org-managed licences">
        Org-managed Copilot licences see output-only tokens forever — the user-level Billing API
        endpoint is empty for them. This is a GitHub limitation, not a budi one. The local-tail
        token counts still work and give you relative cost trends.
      </Callout>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="caveats" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">Caveats</h2>
      <ul class="text-fg-muted space-y-2 text-sm leading-relaxed">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Without a PAT, cost is based on output-only tokens priced through budi's pricing manifest —
          useful as a trend line but not dollar-accurate.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          VS Code must be May-2026+ build for the local session files to include token metadata. Older
          builds lack the structured data budi needs.
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5">
          <span
            aria-hidden="true"
            class="bg-accent mt-[7px] inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full"></span>
          Copilot Chat in Cursor is tracked by the Cursor tailer (via SQLite), not the Copilot Chat tailer.
          See <a href="/docs/providers/cursor/" class="link-underline hover:text-fg">Cursor</a> for details.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2 id="verify" class="text-fg mb-3 text-xl font-semibold tracking-tight">How to verify</h2>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mb-4 leading-relaxed">
        After installing budi, open VS Code, use Copilot Chat, and then run:
      </p>
      <CopyableCommand command="budi doctor" variant="compact" />
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        Look for the Copilot Chat tailer in the output:
      </p>
      <pre
        class="card mt-3 overflow-x-auto p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"><code class="text-fg">✓ Daemon running (pid 12345, port 7878)
✓ Copilot Chat tailer: active
  Path: ~/Library/Application Support/Code/User/workspaceStorage/
  Last event: 6s ago
  GitHub PAT: configured ✓
✓ All checks passed.</code></pre>
      <p class="text-fg-muted mt-4 leading-relaxed">
        If you haven't configured a PAT yet, the output will show:
      </p>
      <pre
        class="card mt-3 overflow-x-auto p-5 font-mono text-sm leading-relaxed"><code class="text-fg">✓ Copilot Chat tailer: active
  GitHub PAT: not configured (output-only tokens)
  Hint: budi config set github.pat &lt;token&gt;</code></pre>
    </section>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
